26/* This does not include any relocation information, but should be
27 good enough for GDB or objdump to read the file. */
28
29static reloc_howto_type dummy =
30 HOWTO (0, /* type */
31 0, /* rightshift */
32 0, /* size (0 = byte, 1 = short, 2 = long) */
33 0, /* bitsize */
34 FALSE, /* pc_relative */
35 0, /* bitpos */
36 complain_overflow_dont, /* complain_on_overflow */
37 NULL, /* special_function */
38 "UNKNOWN", /* name */
39 FALSE, /* partial_inplace */
40 0, /* src_mask */
41 0, /* dst_mask */
42 FALSE); /* pcrel_offset */
43
44static bfd_boolean
45elf_generic_info_to_howto (bfd *abfd ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
46 arelent *bfd_reloc,
47 Elf_Internal_Rela *elf_reloc ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
48{
49 bfd_reloc->howto = &dummy;
50 return TRUE;
51}
52
53static bfd_boolean
54elf_generic_info_to_howto_rel (bfd *abfd ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
55 arelent *bfd_reloc,
56 Elf_Internal_Rela *elf_reloc ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
57{
58 bfd_reloc->howto = &dummy;
59 return TRUE;
60}
61
62static void
63check_for_relocs (bfd * abfd, asection * o, void * failed)
64{
65 if ((o->flags & SEC_RELOC) != 0)
66 {
67 Elf_Internal_Ehdr *ehdrp;
68
69 ehdrp = elf_elfheader (abfd);
70 /* xgettext:c-format */
71 _bfd_error_handler (_("%pB: relocations in generic ELF (EM: %d)"),
72 abfd, ehdrp->e_machine);
73
74 bfd_set_error (bfd_error_wrong_format);
75 * (bfd_boolean *) failed = TRUE;
76 }
77}
78
79static bfd_boolean
80elf32_generic_link_add_symbols (bfd *abfd, struct bfd_link_info *info)
81{
82 bfd_boolean failed = FALSE;
83
84 /* Check if there are any relocations. */
85 bfd_map_over_sections (abfd, check_for_relocs, & failed);
86
87 if (failed)
88 return FALSE;
89 return bfd_elf_link_add_symbols (abfd, info);
90}
